Absa Premiership side Cape Town City on Friday announced that attacker Surprise Ralani has signed a 1-year contract extension to remain at the club until 2021. The Citizens made the announcement on their official Twitter account and shared their delight to have tied down the winger for another year. The 32-year-old winger has so far made 21 appearances in the Absa Premiership, impressively scoring three goals with eight assists. "The club is delighted to have signed a new contract with Surprise Ralani. The winger is extending his stay until June 2021! "Dear Spiro, hereâ€™s to another year of magic," the club tweeted. 